main event: Miss Elizabeth W. Laeburg reported observing two unidentified objects in the sky over her home near Laeburg, Virginia.
interesting points: The objects were described as circular in shape and had a metallic-like appearance., The objects were about the size of a baseball at arm's length., The sighting lasted for about 1 minute before the objects disappeared from view., The observer noted that the objects changed in volume and intensity without fluctuating in color., The conclusion of the report stated insufficient information to establish the identity of the objects.
witness description: Miss Elizabeth W. Laeburg observed the objects 5 miles south of Laeburg
